Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.48,0:01:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel great!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.66,0:01:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will ya switch with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.08,0:01:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost the scissors paper rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.69,0:02:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there till the next telephone pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.00,0:02:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But where's the next pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You finally noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.00,0:02:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't break out of line!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything happen to you guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.63,0:02:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's going to be my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.39,0:02:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I get fired, how would Rika-chan and I live?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.38,0:02:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.55,0:02:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, can't they act as a group?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.76,0:02:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now now. The students are enjoying a leave from study.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you be generous to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.29,0:02:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind, but just to imagine what you as...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.94,0:02:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,vice principal would have to go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.92,0:02:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean would have to go through?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.36,0:02:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that a very rare butterfly lives in this mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.35,0:02:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For my and my wife's future, I intend to find the butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.70,0:03:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who can't act as a group?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.02,0:03:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids. What's so good about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.40,0:03:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to go through this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.69,0:03:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Field trips are for elementary kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.17,0:03:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it up. That's the peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.86,0:03:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the use of getting there? It's just a mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.06,0:03:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it. I can't go anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.10,0:03:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't we use that in this kind of situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.77,0:03:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.07,0:03:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.57,0:03:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do that! What's the point of a field trip if you don't walk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.24,0:04:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to let your younger sister suffer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.64,0:04:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My legs hurt! I can't walk! I can't stand it! Forget it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.79,0:04:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe her...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.59,0:04:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tomomi, why don't you girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.15,0:04:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Matsunaga, where do you think you're going without telling the group leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.27,0:04:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope they aren't going to teleport...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.26,0:04:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ought to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.62,0:04:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. Hey, don't teleport now! What if somebody sees ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noda-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.61,0:04:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.54,0:05:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not the peak, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy. We came pretty far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.73,0:05:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gonna be hard to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.09,0:05:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be easy if we use the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.06,0:05:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi, stop hiding, and come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Tomomi go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If something happened to her, it's all your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.26,0:06:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you find her with telepathy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.87,0:06:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tomomi! Tomomi, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tomomi, answer me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Morning, Mikage...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.50,0:06:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tomomi!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.99,0:06:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you OK?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.05,0:06:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.57,0:06:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank god...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did she say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's badly hurt and she's dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.89,0:06:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a joke, get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Joke?... YOU!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.78,0:06:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, gotta catch up with everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.82,0:06:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tomomi, can you get back on your own?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.46,0:06:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No problem. See you at the peak.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and go by yourself. I'll go on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:06:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.16,0:07:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could he leave behind a girl by herself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.24,0:07:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even see the viewing lounge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.87,0:07:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this's the right way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.52,0:07:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading south.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.75,0:07:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.87,0:07:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The leaves. The trees usually have leaves towards sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind you, it also depend on wind too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.23,0:07:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know pretty boring things, don't ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.16,0:07:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you know, get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.05,0:08:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10.0 points! Tomomi Matsunaga does it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always wanted to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.32,0:08:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You have two hours of free time. Enjoy the nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, Noda, where are ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing that he hasn't shown up, ...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume he doesn't need his lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.67,0:08:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you chewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just something to get some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.66,0:08:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna eat grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to drink, you can have water out of my canteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.32,0:08:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.46,0:08:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's OK. I'm fine with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.06,0:08:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't stand seeing you chewing grass. You look disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disgusting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.27,0:08:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how Mikage is doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.71,0:09:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're disgusting! Get it, you Neanderthal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.57,0:09:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you eat up your lunch, you're gonna have to eat this, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.29,0:09:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mikage! Mikage!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.46,0:09:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Tomomi. This guy's eating grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.10,0:09:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I'm telling ya you can have my water. Hold it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.44,0:09:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fight too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.02,0:09:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you be a good boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Aren't we heading south?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... you see. We're off course a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.31,0:09:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? But you sounded so confident!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do about it? We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.56,0:09:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe how careless you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I can't stand about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I believed in this dummy, we're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.37,0:09:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't over react.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.89,0:09:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying we should take the road to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.81,0:10:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Road to the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.18,0:10:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This creepy trail?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't like it, don't come. I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all your fault in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you make a mistake again, you'll pay for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.40,0:10:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I gotta climb this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.71,0:10:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.47,0:11:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,EYECATCHER
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.76,0:11:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ought to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.35,0:11:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, can I go through the forest and get to the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.99,0:11:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting deeper into the forest, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.43,0:11:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what a cute bunny!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:11:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so special about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the first time I've seen a wild one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.02,0:12:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one I've seen is the one in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at her when we could run into something bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.51,0:12:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.47,0:12:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Sing me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.04,0:12:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice principal, I can't seem to find Noda-kun and Matsunaga-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.27,0:12:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are Noda-kun and the Matsunaga sisters?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.25,0:12:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has anybody seen them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:12:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They headed back, because they're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.92,0:13:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.60,0:13:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.31,0:13:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but where did they go?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.74,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it. There're bears around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.66,0:13:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.62,0:13:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.85,0:13:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the sun. Even if we get to the peak, they would be gone by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.16,0:14:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.63,0:14:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.05,0:14:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there's a bridge. So, this's the right trail after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.71,0:14:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I'm back on the trail, I can get to the peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.45,0:14:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And once I'm with Tomomi, I can get to anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look safe. It hasn't been in use for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better than getting lost by following you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.09,0:14:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, have it your way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There're bears on the other side, too. Get back, Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't he cross the bridge? What a wimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn Mikage.. Get back! The bears!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.67,0:15:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't she listen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.81,0:15:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, the rope is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.07,0:15:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.47,0:16:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So hot. What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a concussion. No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.67,0:16:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just gimme something to cool it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what would...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.07,0:16:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.22,0:16:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this. How should I tell Tomomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:16:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There seems to be something, but is it just my feeling?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.56,0:17:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.85,0:17:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pain's going away. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.23,0:17:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh good. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you look cute when you're being a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.65,0:17:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey stop joking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.49,0:17:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But are you positive about the bears?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.39,0:17:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am. Remember I took a different route?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were fresh bear tracks on the trail we should've taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.97,0:17:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there were claw marks all over the forest. That's why I made you sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.07,0:17:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bears are pretty nervous animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we make noise, they wouldn't approach us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.58,0:17:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:18:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it. Do you think humans would come around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.99,0:18:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.32,0:18:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this shrub?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.51,0:18:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.73,0:18:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noda-kun, Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.14,0:18:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.34,0:18:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm glad you two are OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.64,0:18:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.19,0:18:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noda thought you were a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.26,0:18:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.48,0:19:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was following me after all. Let's teleport, Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.30,0:19:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.06,0:19:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.16,0:19:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.22,0:19:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We gotta do it, or we're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.54,0:19:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push it! I'll deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dummy. How can you beat a bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.84,0:20:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a place I ended up at.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear I heard the Matsunaga sisters voice over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.27,0:20:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are. We were looking all over for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.23,0:20:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, get back to the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.77,0:20:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.70,0:20:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.79,0:20:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where were you? With Tomomi-chan and Mikage-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now I guess I'll give him a bit more credit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.78,0:21:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I now know why you fell for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.27,0:21:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thats unfair, how could you three go play around by yourselves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.63,0:21:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind you, there's no way he can beat Kurashige-sempai.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.23,0:21:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice principal, what seems to be troubling you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.69,0:21:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still think we left somebody behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.71,0:21:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly not. The Matsunaga sisters are back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.49,0:21:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure we left...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.21,0:21:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We forgot Kageura-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.03,0:21:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it! You can't leave me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.79,0:21:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miracle Girls here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First love's such a beautiful memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.61,0:21:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.57,0:21:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met an old lady by the beach in search of her first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.24,0:21:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's find the first love for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.49,0:22:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next on Miracle Girls:\N"First Love in Mirage"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a tale that's tied with an old scarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.88,0:22:09.30,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:12.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.52,0:22:15.93,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we had a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:19.15,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:35.79,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days when kindness is so close
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:39.08,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,, that you can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.38,0:22:52.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we know it better than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:59.02,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,When we can't say "I'm sorry,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.10,0:23:06.07,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we send out feelings through the little fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.82,0:23:12.83,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Going over the tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:15.74,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we want to be honest to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:21.17,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause the sky deserves a rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:24.21,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:27.67,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:30.76,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:34.14,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,are better than one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.15,0:22:25.65,credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ending Song\N"There has to be Both of Us"\N("Futarijanakya Dame Nano")\NBy Dio
